quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  3,141,"And (for) God to purify/clarify/cleanse those who believed, and to annihilate/wipe off the disbelievers"
  3,142,"Or (have) you thought/supposed that you enter the Paradise, and God did not (E) know, those who struggled/did utmost from you, and He knows the patient"
  3,143,"And you had been wishing/desiring the death, from before that you meet/find it, so you had seen it and you (are) looking"
  3,144,"And Mohammad is not except a messenger, had passed/expired from before him the messengers, so if he died, or (he was) killed, you turned/returned on your heels , and whom turns/returns, on his two heels, so he will never/not harm God, a thing, and God will reward the thankful/grateful"
  3,145,"And it was not to a self that to die except with God`s permission, a decree/destiny/fate delayed , and who wants/wills the present world`s reward, We give him from it, and who wants/wills the end`s (other life`s) reward, We give him from it, and We will reward the thankful/grateful"
  3,146,"And how many from a prophet fought/killed with him many knowledgeable Lord worshippers? So they did not weaken/enfeeble for (what) struck them in God`s sake , and they did not weaken, and they did not become humiliated/disgraced, and God loves/likes the patient"
  3,147,"And their saying was not, except that they said: \"Our Lord, forgive for us our crimes and our spoilage/wastefulness in our matter/affair, and affix/make our feet firm, and give us victory/aid over the nation, the disbelieving"
  3,148,"So God gave them the present world`s reward, and the end`s (other life`s) beautiful/good reward, and God loves/likes the good doers"